## **Feed Configuration Documentation**

### **YouTube Feed Configuration**

* **name**: `youtube`  
* **description**:  
  Discover and showcase your favorite YouTube videos seamlessly in your feed. Stay connected with trending content and share your highlights effortlessly.

**regex**:  
r"^(https?://)?(www\\.)?(youtube\\.com/(u(ser)?|@)\[/\\w-\]+)(/(videos|playlists|community|streams|shorts))?$"

* **Accepts**: YouTube channel URLs (user, @handle) with optional sections like `/videos`, `/shorts`, etc.

### **Vimeo Feed Configuration**

* **name**: `vimeo`  
* **description**:  
  Curate and share top Vimeo videos with your audience. Immerse in creative content and inspire your feed with high-quality productions from Vimeo.

**regex**:  
r"^(?:https://vimeo\\.com/)?(?\<id\>.+)$"

* **Accepts**: Vimeo profile or channel identifiers, with or without the full URL.

### **Instagram Feed Configuration**

* **Accepts**: Instagram profile URLs or usernames.
